<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-01-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-01-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="752" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d752">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">McCormick</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">St.
                                        Petersburg</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-01-11"><hi rend="italic">January 11,
                                1905</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. McCormick reports that sworn statements from the owners only of the
                            cargo on the <hi rend="italic">Arabia</hi> relating to facts stated in
                            Department’s telegram of the 7th instant are required for formal
                            presentation to the admiralty court.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>